rComments: I found her fantastic, as a Spanish prof. Really knew her stuff and was always able to answer questions and explain grammatical concepts really well. For the Don Quixote half course, she knew the work inside out and was very enthusiastic. She made the class enjoyable, I got an amazing grade because she kept me interested. Take her Spanish classes!

Did you like high school? Then you're gonna love Prof Iglesias's courses! Being constantly reminded about the exam, "class", get only a superficial analysis, and then get a "beautiful exam" on which she "spent a lot of time", where dates of birth of the authors are worth 1/5 of the mark. Mmm, high school. What a waste of my time.
